Police have filed charges against a man who used his gun to threaten people at an Andiccio pizzeria in Johannesburg. Management at the shop says the man ordered focaccia and then complained over the lack of cheese. JOHANNESBURG - Police have filed charges against a man who used his gun to threaten people at an Andiccio pizzeria in Johannesburg. Management at the shop say the man ordered a focaccia and then complained over the lack of cheese. The man argued with a number of customers who came to the staff's defense. He took out a firearm before leaving the premises and allegedly discharging two shots outside. Police are investigating.